<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="582396c8-3f33-5816-943a-8208d50817f5" activityNameId="919cdfc8-d945-49a3-a871-8e43db19279f" parentActivityId="a2591782-2d08-4531-9f76-bf2ddd632056" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1" energyValues="0">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">clinker production</activityName>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Portland cement clinker</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">dry rotary kiln</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">clinker</synonym>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The dataset includes the preparation of raw materials (drying, grinding and homogeneization) and fuels (drying-grinding), preheating and precalcining steps, clinker production in the rotary kiln, cooling and storage in silos. Water is used mainly for dust control. Auxiliary materials for factory maintenance are considered. Air emissions stem mainly from the rotary kiln exhaust.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends with the storage after cooling of the produced clinker. It includes the whole manufacturing processes to produce clinker (raw material provision, grinding and mixing; rotary kiln process. No administration is included.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The dataset describes the production of Portland cement clinker in Tunisia. </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Clinker is the main constituent of Portland cement and also the main responsible for its environmental impacts. Clinker is made by sintering a mixture composed mainly of limestone and clay (called “raw meal”) at temperatures up to 1450 °C. Both primary and secondary fuels are used to this end. After sintering, clinker nodules have a diameter between 5 mm and 25 mm.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2"></text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">Clinker consists of various calcium silicates including alite (3CaO.SiO2 or “C3S”) and belite (2CaO.SiO2 or “C2S”). Tricalcium aluminate (3CaO.Al2O3 or “C3A”) and calcium aluminoferrite (4CaO.Al2O3.Fe2O3 or “C4AF”) are other common components, added to reduce the sintering temperature of the calcium silicates. For special cement types, such as low heat and sulfate resistant, it is necessary to limit the amount of tricalcium aluminate formed.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">Pyroprocessing, and cement preparation: - Raw material extraction - Crushing of raw material - Pre-homogenization and raw meal grinding</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="5"> - Pre-calcining - Production of clinker - Cooling and storage - Clinker grinding and the cement manufacturing process - Milling of cement</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="6"></text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="7">After the kiln, clinker is cooled and stored in silos. Clinker production plants are usually integrated with cement plants.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="8">Primary data were gathered from one cement manufacturer in Tunisia who informed the total values of inputs and outputs related to clinker production in 2019 considering all their clinker production sites. All types of flows were reported, namely: primary and secondary raw materials and fuels, auxiliary materials, electricity consumption, water consumption and air emissions (from emissions monitoring reports). It corresponds to 15% of the market share, considered a good representativeness level.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="9">SOURCES:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="10"> Schorcht, F., Kourti, I., Scalet, B.M., Roudier, S., Sancho, L.D., 2013. Best available techniques (BAT) reference document for the production of cement, lime and magnesium oxide. Eur. Comm. Jt. Res. Cent. Inst. Prospect. Technol. Stud. Rep. EUR 26129 EN Luxemb. Publ. Off. Eur. Union</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="11">Boesch, M.E., Koehler, A., Hellweg, S., 2009. Model for Cradle-to-Gate Life Cycle Assessment of Clinker Production. Environ. Sci. Technol. 43, 7578–7583. https://doi.org/10.1021/es900036e</text>
          <imageUrl index="12">https://db3.ecoinvent.org/images/bd0062b7-f504-4b77-b43a-3a83c12158e4</imageUrl>
          <imageUrl index="13">https://db3.ecoinvent.org/images/4015964a-30e6-4523-a434-066662163063</imageUrl>
        </generalComment>
        <tag>combined production</tag>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="36cd730c-4485-4fe9-8efe-8850f771796d">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2394:Manufacture of cement, lime and plaster</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <classification classificationId="d1458e41-6104-4994-adfb-95a5b47e3841">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">EcoSpold01Categories</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">construction materials/binder</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="133fc02a-7d7e-11de-9ae2-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">TN</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents production of clinker for Tunisia. Data come from one cement manufacturer in Tunisia.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Current technology for clinker production in Tunisian dry kilns, considering various fuel types.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">In Tunisia, cement plants use dry kilns with preheater and precalciner, being a total of nine cement plants (eight gray clinker and one white clinker) (dry). This dataset represents data for gray clinker from one cement manufacturer. Regarding fuel types, 88,1% are fossil fuels (petroleum coke), 11% biomass (olive poumace) and 0,9% natural gas (data from 2019).</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">Sources: </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3"></text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="4">Single Market Profile: TUNISIA 2022. </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="5">Institut National de la Statistique. Statistiques Tunisie. BULLETIN MENSUEL DES STATISTIQUES. Janvier 2020</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2019-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The dataset represents a cement plant in Tunisia. The time period is set according to the historical data (2019) collected from the industry.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Data correspond to 2019.</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
